'''''Homo politicus''''' is a [[Pejorative|derogatory]] term for the stereotypical behaviour of people in a political settings.

It is also used in public policy theory to denote an individual who, supposedly, acts in the public good.  In this usage, it is juxtaposed with "Homo Economicus" who is self-interested.  Thus, Homo Politicus is the version of man that is interested in the public good.

